history.content:
CS162: Yesterday, we added one additional discussion section (106) and increased the lecture capacity by 26 and might do so one more time in the next few days.  **NEW Wed 10:30PM**  We added the final additional discussion section and increased enrollment to 260 .

CS189: We have funding and permission to increase combined initial enrollment capacity for 189/289A to 450 students and will add 3-4 new discussion sections soon.

**NEW Wed 4pm** CS170: We have added 4 discussion sections (108-110 and 113) and increased enrollment limit on the lecture to 520.

Your best strategy for the above classes is to keep your eyes on the schedule and drop and re-add one of those new discussion sections as they become available.

Note that in 162 you need to be enrolled in a discussion section that you don't have a conflict with via calcentral but actual discussion assignments will be reshuffled in the actual class based on your availability and that of other members of your project group.

Also, CS169 has additional capacity and interested students should waitlist the class and go to the first lecture to find team-mates.

----

NOTE:  The block on non-major enrollment will be lifted on a class by class basis ~ 24 hours after final changes have been made to class schedules and enrollment limits starting.  This will start tomorrow morning with 188 and 189 and be done no later than Sunday night. (I won't have time to answer specific questions about individual classes etc. in regards to this but it will all be done (for any class that is not instructor permission only) by no later than Sunday evening and so waitlists will be processed for everyone in order beginning no later than Monday morning (8/29).

NOTE2 (Friday 11:30AM 8/26): Except for 160/260A, enrollment screens prioritizing majors have been lifted as of this morning (11 days after we would normally have done so).  For 160/260A, I still have some information I need to gather about the balance between the size of the grad and undergrad enrollments so it might take until Monday or Tuesday to make that shift.
